M|Em D|tx|**The em dash (—) has become one of the most reliable markers of AI-generated cn.**
M|Em D|tx|Em dashes are longer than hyphens (-) and are used for emphasis, interruptions, or parenthetical information. While they have legitimate uses in writing, AI md drastically overuse them.
M|Why |it|AI md were trained on edited books, academic papers, and style guides where em dashes appear frequently
M|Why |it|AI uses em dashes as a shortcut for sentence variety instead of commas, colons, or parentheses
M|Why |it|Most human writers rarely use em dashes bc they don't exist as a standard keyboard key
M|Why |it|The overuse is so consistent that it has become the unofficial signature of ChatGPT writing
M|What|tx|\| Instead of \| Use \|
M|What|tx|\|------------\|-----\|
M|What|tx|\| The results—which were surprising—showed... \| The results, which were surprising, showed... \|
M|What|tx|\| This approach—unlike traditional methods—allows... \| This approach, unlike traditional methods, allows... \|
M|What|tx|\| The study found—as expected—that... \| The study found, as expected, that... \|
M|What|tx|\| Communication skills—both written and verbal—are essential \| Communication skills (both written and verbal) are essential \|
M|Guid|it|Use commas for most parenthetical information
M|Guid|it|Use colons to introduce explanations or lists
M|Guid|it|Use parentheses for supplementary information
M|Guid|it|Reserve em dashes for rare, deliberate emphasis only
M|Guid|it|If you find yourself using more than one em dash per page, revise
M|Guid|tx|---
